  <title>Gio.InputStream</title>
  <synopsis><code>
const Gio = imports.gi.Gio;

let inputStream = new Gio.InputStream();
  </code></synopsis>
  <p><link xref="Gio.InputStream"/> has functions to read from a stream (<link xref="Gio.InputStream.read"/>),
to close a stream (<link xref="Gio.InputStream.close"/>) and to skip some content
(<link xref="Gio.InputStream.skip"/>).</p>  <p>To copy the content of an input stream to an output stream without
manually handling the reads and writes, use <link xref="Gio.OutputStream.splice"/>.</p>  <p>All of these functions have async variants too.</p>

